About this hotel

Featuring wrought-steel balconies, mosaic tile floors and stucco walls, this elegant riad-style hotel is a 4-minute walk from Jemaa el-Fnaa square, a 14-minute walk from the 16th-century El Badi Palace and 5 km from Menara gardens.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    Eric T8 months ago on Google
    5/5
    A peaceful, authentic Riad with a lovely breakfast and VERY close to Jemaa El-Fna Square. Some listings state that the rooms have TVs. This is not the case, apart from the Mogador Suite (Which is beautiful by the way), but you don't visit …
    A peaceful, authentic Riad with a lovely breakfast and VERY close to Jemaa El-Fna Square. Some listings state that the rooms have TVs. This is not the case, apart from the Mogador Suite (Which is beautiful by the way), but you don't visit marrakesh to watch TV..
    The Mogador Suite and rest of the Riad is full of original features, traditional designs and techniques. Everything from the furniture, artwork, mosaic tiles and painted ceilings lends itself to an 'Arabian Nights' atmosphere. I actually saw a lot of the same features from Riad Jnane Mogador in some of the city's museums.
    The staff were graceful and unobtrusive. The terrace is peaceful and a wonderful place to eat breakfast whilst looking over the rooftops of Marrakesh and listening to the call to prayer.
    I'll definitely be returning to the Mogador Suite soon!

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakesh’s original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    Featuring wrought-steel balconies, mosaic tile floors and stucco walls, this elegant riad-style hotel is a 4-minute walk from Jemaa el-Fnaa square, a 14-minute walk from the 16th-century El Badi Palace and 5 km from Menara gardens. …

    Furnished with steel-framed beds and handmade wood tables and desks, the traditional rooms offer free Wi-Fi and satellite TV. Polished suites come with 4-poster beds, minibars and terraces, plus living areas with sofas. Room service is offered 24/7.

    Breakfast is included. Other amenities consist of a snug restaurant and a spa, as well as an ornate lounge with a fireplace.
